  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 200 degrees Celsius.",
    "Pat the cod dry and season with sea salt, black pepper, and smoked paprika.",
    "Heat olive oil in an oven-safe skillet over medium heat, add garlic and onion, and cook until fragrant.",
    "Stir in tomatoes and bell pepper, simmer for 5 minutes to blend flavors.",
    "Place the seasoned cod fillets on top of the sauce and spoon some sauce over the fish.",
    "Bake uncovered for 15 minutes until the fish flakes easily with a fork.",
    "Remove from oven and drizzle fresh lemon juice over the fillets.",
    "Serve hot, spooning extra sauce onto each portion."
